  <li><strong>Elementary OS</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>To narrow the list of <em>things-to-test</em> I set up some polls on Google+.  As an Arch Linux user I‚Äôm attracted to minimalism, so my ROM choices are biased there.  But, I try to contribute to FOSS where / when I can so what better place to begin than its community?  In addition to dozens of ROMs, there is also a dizzying array of I/O schedulers and CPU governors (<a href="http://forum.xda-developers.com/general/general/ref-to-date-guide-cpu-governors-o-t3048957">XDA has a nice list here</a>).  Some governors even have published custom configuration ‚Äúprofiles.‚Äù  Obviously I can‚Äôt test everything.</p>

<p><a href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/+AustinHaedicke/posts/XhiBqsZFFvk">Voted ROMS</a>:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Chroma (&gt; 62)</strong></li>
  <li><strong>Krexus (&gt; 14)</strong></li>
  <li>Exodus (&gt; 8)</li>
  <li>Vanir (&gt; 2)</li>
