</ul>

<p>My (imperfect) testing process will go something like this:  Flash a ROM and run benchmarks on the <strong>bold</strong> features listed herein at their default values. Then, begin tracking battery and CPU usage as well as uptime. Next, run benchmarks on altrenate I/O schedulers or CPU profiles, reset to default settings. Minimum runtime goal is 50 hours to try and compensate for day-to-day variance and offset the benchmark spikes.</p>

